      • encodeDelta

        public void encodeDelta(int a2,
                        double[] s2,
                        int a1,
                        double[] s1)
        Encodes a delta for s2 given s1. Assumes that the union of s1 and s2 contains no missing elements.
        Parameters:
        a2 - Alignment of the new vintage, s2.
        s2 - New vintage series for which we would like to generate a delta.
        a1 - Alignment of the previous vintage, s1.
        s1 - Previous vintage series to be differenced against.
        Complexity:
        O(n)

      • decodeDelta

        public double[] decodeDelta()
        Decodes a vintage series the vintage node instance.
        Returns:
        A decoded vintage series
        Complexity:
        k*mean(n), where k is the number of vintages and mean(n) is the average vintage length.
